#Text=The New York Knicks ( 15 - 18 ) defeated the Detroit Pistons ( 17 - 15 ) 108 - 96 on Tuesday .
#Text=It was a game where both teams went against some recent trends and produced some atypical numbers as a result .
#Text=New York came into the contest in a bit of a funk on offense , having failed to hit the century mark in four straight games .
#Text=They were able to comfortably surpass that mark with a surprisingly solid shooting night .

#Text=The Knicks had managed to only drain 43 percent of their field - goal attempts on the season ( fifth - worst in the league ) , and their 33 percent metric from beyond the arc ranked them 24th out of 30 teams in that category .
#Text=Tuesday , they posted stellar 54 and 50 percent figures , respectively , while also outmuscling a Pistons team down low that features Andre Drummond as its centerpiece .
#Text=New York outscored Detroit in the paint 46 - 36 , while also besting them on the glass by a margin of 36 - 24 .
#Text=Considering that the Pistons had entered Tuesday as one of the top rebounding teams in the league , the feat was especially noteworthy .
#Text=The visitors did receive an impressively productive night from their starting lineup , with four players tallying double - digit points .
#Text=Veteran Ersan Ilysova led the way with 19 points , six rebounds , an assist and three steals , while Marcus Morris and Reggie Jackson complemented him with a pair of 17 - point efforts .
#Text=The latter came away just one assist short of a double - double .
#Text=Andre Drummond also fell just short of that mark , but when he does , it 's breaking news .

#Text=The Pistons ' center had managed double - digit points and rebounds in all but four of Detroit 's 31 games coming in , and was coming off a 22 - point , 22 - rebound outing against Boston on Saturday .
#Text=However , Robin Lopez showed why he 's been one of the toughest defensive centers in the league this year by limiting Drummond to only 13 points and nine boards .
#Text=Detroit fell to 17 - 15 and currently resides in fourth place in the Eastern Conference 's Central Division .
#Text=They head home for a New Year 's Eve matchup versus the Timberwolves .
#Text=The Knicks ' attack was spearheaded by Carmelo Anthony , who impressively overcame Morris ' shutdown defense against small forwards to tally 24 points , six rebounds , six assists and a steal .
#Text=The Pistons had come into the game as the top - ranked unit against opposing threes , but Anthony displayed the pedigree that still makes him one of the most prolific scorers in the league .

#Text=Three other starters joined him in double - figure scoring , with Jose Calderon ( 15 points ) , Kristaps Porzingis ( 10 points ) and Lopez ( 11 points , seven rebounds , two assists , a steal and six blocks ) making solid contributions .
#Text=Derrick Williams was outstanding in pacing the Knicks ' bench with 18 points , four rebounds and an assist .
#Text=New York improved to 15 - 18 and currently resides in third place in the Eastern Conference 's Atlantic Division .
#Text=They head to Chicago for a New Year 's Day showdown with the Bulls .
